thou not made the Almighty almost weary of Correcting <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum" n="26">25</fw>
                  <pb n="15"/>
                  <lb/>
thee? and <normalised orig="shewest" auto="true">show</normalised> thou <normalised orig="lovest" auto="true">love</normalised> thy Sin too well to <lb/>
be easily torn from it? <normalised orig="Fifthly" auto="true">Fiftly</normalised>, And finally how mischievous <lb/>
have the effects of thy transgressions been? <lb/>
They have dishonoured God, disgraced thy Religion, <lb/>
<normalised orig="incouraged" auto="true">encouraged</normalised> the wicked to persevere, incited the innocent <lb/>
to follow thy steps, and offended weak and tender <lb/>
<normalised orig="Chrisitans" auto="false">Christians</normalised>. This is indeed a sad story, and if we rightly <lb/>
apprehend it, may make the best to cry out with trembling <lb/>
